            <thetext>Currently, qx.test.lang.Json tests the emulated JSON no matter if native JSON is available. However, qx.lang.Json uses the native JSON when available. To ensure consistency across browsers, including those using the native JSON, tests should verify qx.lang.Json itself.

A quick test revealed that some tests fail in some browsers as soon as qx.lang.Json is tested. This seems to be due to very strict tests revealing (mostly white space) differences in native implementations. Those tests should be formulated more liberally.</thetext>
